  <skos:Concept rdf:about="http://purl.org/heritagedata/schemes/599/concepts/168137">
    <skos:scopeNote xml:lang="en">An aircraft lifted by gas bags, containing hydrogen or helium, but propelled by engines. Also known as a dirigible balloon, firm and streamlined in shape and incapable of high speeds. Used extensively during the First World War.</skos:scopeNote>
